<body>
    <div class="container">
        <%- include('../partials/header') %>
        <%- include('../partials/nav') %>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Error Handling</h2>
            <p>Understanding uncaughtException vs unhandledRejection and proper error handling.</p>
            
            <h3>uncaughtException</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre><code>// Synchronous errors not caught
process.on('uncaughtException', (error) => {
  console.error('Uncaught exception:', error);
  // WHY: Log and exit - app is in unknown state
  process.exit(1);
});

// Example
throw new Error('Uncaught!');</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p><strong>When:</strong> Synchronous code throws error without try/catch</p>
            
            <h3>unhandledRejection</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre><code>// Promise rejection not handled
process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason, promise) => {
  console.error('Unhandled rejection:', reason);
  // WHY: Log and handle - app might still be OK
});

// Example
Promise.reject(new Error('Unhandled!'));</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p><strong>When:</strong> Promise rejection without .catch()</p>
            
            <div class="key-points">
                <h3>Best Practices:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Always handle promise rejections</li>
                    <li>Use try/catch for async/await</li>
                    <li>Log errors before exiting</li>
                    <li>Graceful shutdown on uncaughtException</li>
                    <li>Monitor unhandledRejection (might indicate bugs)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
    </div>
